# Changelog
All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]
### Added
- [Python] Support for odt format
- [Python] An intial set-up wizard that defines the logo & other company meta data, as well as the file format
- [DevOps] An automated bot to make new changelogs or at least help in the making of them.

### Changed
- [Python-Backend] Sectioned off the number-word functions into its own file (for ease of re-use)

### Fixed

### Removed

## [p.0.4] 'The Chungus Awakens'
### Added
- [Python-GUI] Removals functionality.
- [Python-GUI] Additions functionality.
- [Python-GUI] Previous page functionality.
- [Python-GUI] Next Page functionality.
- [Python-GUI] Removals functionality.
- [Python-GUI] data checking functionality.

### Changed
- [Python-GUI] Improved the UX by setting everything up in frames.
- [Python-GUI] Refactored the clear options so that the buttons indicate whether we need to clear a few or all
- [Python] Sectioned off the docxBuilder function to support micro-servicing
- [Python-GUI] Sectioned off the code into component functions for readability and reusability's sake.
- [Python-Backend] Capitalised the SUCCESS and FAILURE parts of the relevant print statements.

### Fixed
- [Python] An error in the set_invoice_number function which did not allow it to update the invoice number
- [Python-Backend] An error that in the multi-functionality with GUI. Lack of functionality for it, plus I forgot lists are 0-indexed.

### Removed
- [Java] Any hope of a java version

## [p.0.3] 'Attack of the dot ini'
### Added
- [Python] Support for configuration file
- [Python] Added an os check to ensure a config file

### Changed
- [Python] Various items to support the configuration file

### Removed
- [Python] Dependence on a bodge-y docx file for invoice storage
- [Python] Remove the second ask or the 'Are you Sure' from the initial request

## [p.0.2] 'Rise of the Lists'
### Added
- [Python] Support for multi-item functionality.

### Changed
- [Python] Various items to enable the multi-item functionality.

### Fixed
- [Python] The number-word converter

### Removed


## [p.0.1] 'Tkinter: A New Hope.'
### Added
- [Python] Several new functions
- [Python] Semi-temporary grid feature
- [Python] Buttons, Labels, Entries.
- [Python] Progress indicators

### Changed
- [Python] The default variables in the Document Builder script

### Removed
- [Python] Removed support for automatic command line variable assignage

# The non purely python path
## [0.0.8] 'Connection achieved !'
### Added
- [Java] GUI forwarding of input to the CLI

### Changed
- [Java] Recoded and refactored the CLI code.

### Removed
- [Java] Deleted the 'pythonplusjava' class.

## [0.0.7] 'CLI – INTEGRATED'
### Added
- [Java] Java-CMD-Python functionality
- [Python] A lot of scaffolding for the sake of bug-quashing

### Changed
- [Python] main() now has a try and except block which checks for extra command line arguments to use as input, if none, then it continues as normal.

### Removed
- [Python] Recursion as I would prefer it in the Front End. 

### Depreciated
- [Python] Total Amount in words as it is currently not working properly.

### Known Bugs
-[Python] Total Amount does not work with any number.

## [0.0.6] 'Frontend – somewhat – complete'
### Added
- [Java] A GUI to handle all input declarations
- [Java] Input Functionality
- [Java] Validation for all input except a presence check
- [Java] A recursive element

### Removed
- [Python] The recursive element

## [0.0.5] 'Backend – Mostly – Complete'
### Added
- [Python] Support for decimal word conversion
- [Python] Support for integer word conversion
- [Python] get_date() for getting today's date while still being manual in the MS Word Doc
- [Python] More print statements to determine progress.

### Changed
- [Python] All monetary variables have a minimum of 2 characters

## [0.0.4] 'Defaults and Fixing Formats'

### Added
- Defaults, so as to improve testing flow.
- Proper format functionality, so all looks well.
- Empty build_invoice() function in preparation for the upcoming removal of the front-end functionality in the python.

### Fixed
- Formatting of the MS Template Doc to fit better with the necessary document style.
